column9: Looking primarily for customer marketing, customer advocacy, executive engagement/marketing, and customer experience roles and/or project work.

I have: 
- Media training
- Soft Skills
- Experience in various formats of writing (blog, formal, news articles) and copy editing
- Experience giving in-person and online training
- Strong background in:
--- GRC
--- Privacy
--- SDLC processes
- No issue with working long-term, odd hours that accommodate global organizational timezones
- Management experience (though I prefer IC)

I'd love to move into a full time "security awareness" program role. Even if it were only one part of a broader role. 

Going back into GRC is also a very reasonable next step for me

I've had at least some past experience doing almost everything in infosec (NOT pen testing, malware analysis, and threat hunting). I started as a UNIX admin and app dev (perl, php, shell, C, pascal, basic, hypercard...)

I'm comfortable in *NIX command line, and reviewing settings in enterprise apps, but I'm not a "hands-on" engineer or a dev anymore

My focus is on people and process. Proactive risk mitigation, shifting security left, overarching processes, providing guidance and consultation on a myriad of topics, writing policies, etc. I'm great at explaining very complex security topics in simple ways that non-infosec people can understand.

anyway, it's been a pleasure, friends! <3

I just moved to Hawaii last year, so I'm looking for a job that allows me to work remotely. If remote is impossible, I would be happy if I could move and work at the company. I mainly code in Python and go lang.
